Adjust rack to top and bottom positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and
dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.
Halve, peel, and very thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Pick 1 tsp thyme leaves
(@Thyme{¼%ounce}) from stems; reserve remaining sprigs for step 2. Cut
@Roma Tomato{1} into 8 wedges. Halve @Lemon{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add onion and thyme sprigs; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and
softened, ~{10-15%minutes}. (TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion
starts to burn.) Discard sprigs; add half the @Beef Stock Concentrate{2}(half),
@Sugar{1%tablespoon}, and @Butter{2%tablespoon}(half). Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Turn off heat. Transfer to a #small bowl{}; cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of olive
oil, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}(half), salt, and pepper. Roast on
top rack, flipping halfway through, until golden brown and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}. Line a second baking sheet with foil; place
@Bacon{4%ounce} on sheet. Roast on bottom rack until crispy,
~{12-15%minutes}. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Cut top off carton of @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce} to open fully; pour contents
into a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Using a #spoon{} or #spatula{}, scrape any
remaining sauce from carton into bowl. Add remaining stock concentrates; stir to
combine. Microwave until steaming, ~{1%minute}. Whisk in
@Mozzarella Cheese{½%cup} and thyme leaves until smooth and slightly thickened.
Microwave another ~{30%seconds}, then stir again.

In a second #medium bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce} and remaining Fry
Seasoning. Form into two patties, each slightly wider than a @Brioche Buns{2}.
Season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon}
in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired
doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Halve buns; toast until golden.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} and tomato with a large drizzle
of olive oil and lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Microwave
sauce again until warmed, ~{30%seconds}; whisk in remaining @Butter{2%tablespoon}.
Fill buns with patties, caramelized onion, bacon, and some sauce. Serve with
salad, potato wedges, and remaining sauce for dipping on the side.